Source: pcp-gui
Section: utils
Priority: extra
Maintainer: PCP Development Team <pcp@oss.sgi.com>
Uploaders: Nathan Scott <nathans@debian.org>, Anibal Monsalve Salazar <anibal@debian.org>
Build-Depends: autoconf, bison, flex, gawk, xmlto, debhelper (>= 5), libpcp3-dev (>= 3.5.0), libqt4-dev
Standards-Version: 3.9.3

Package: pcp-gui
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Suggests: xvfb, qt4-dev-tools
Recommends: pcp, pcp-doc
Architecture: any
Description: Visualisation tools for the Performance Co-Pilot toolkit
 The PCP GUI package primarily includes visualisation tools for
 monitoring systems using live and archived Performance Co-Pilot
 (PCP) sources.
 .
 These tools have dependencies on graphics libraries which may or
 may not be installed on server machines, so PCP GUI is delivered,
 managed and maintained as a separate (source and binary) package
 to the core PCP infrastructure.

Package: pcp-doc
Section: doc
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Breaks: pcp-gui (<< 1.5.0)
Replaces: pcp-gui (<< 1.5.0)
Recommends: pcp, pcp-gui
Architecture: all
Description: Documentation and tutorial for the Performance Co-Pilot
 The pcp-doc package provides useful information on using and
 configuring the Performance Co-Pilot (PCP) toolkit for system
 level performance management.  It includes tutorials, HOWTOs,
 and other detailed documentation about the internals of core
 PCP utilities and daemons, and the PCP graphical tools.

Package: pcp-gui-testsuite
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, pcp-gui (= ${binary:Version})
Architecture: any
Description: Performance Co-Pilot (PCP) GUI Test Suite
 Quality assurance test suite for Performance Co-Pilot (PCP) GUI.
 .
 Provides a series of tests that exercise the utilities that are a
 part of the PCP GUI package.  Regular users should never have any
 need to install this package, it is for developers and testers.
